[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/661023060","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163#issuecomment-661023060","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163","id":661023060,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY2MTAyMzA2MA==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-07-20T12:58:13Z","updated_at":"2020-07-20T12:58:13Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"Haven't used loguru before, but I got it working with Rich. You were close, the `configure` method takes a list of dicts.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom loguru import logger\r\nfrom rich.logging import RichHandler\r\n\r\nlogger.configure(handlers=[{\"sink\":RichHandler(), \"format\":\"{message}\"}])\r\nlogger.debug(\"This is a debug statement\")\r\nlogger.info(\"This is an info statement\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnly thing I couldn't figure out was how to change loguru date format.","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/661122426","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163#issuecomment-661122426","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163","id":661122426,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY2MTEyMjQyNg==","user":{"login":"leej11","id":17391902,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MzkxOTAy","avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/17391902?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11","html_url":"https://github.com/leej11","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/leej11/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-07-20T15:48:01Z","updated_at":"2020-07-20T15:48:01Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Ah amazing. So I can copy the format argument in the configure method.\r\n\r\nhttps://loguru.readthedocs.io/en/stable/api/logger.html#loguru._logger.Logger.add\r\n\r\nSo I copied the default that loguru has in the link above. So I guess you can move around the YYYY-MM-DD to whatever date format you want?\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom loguru import logger\r\nfrom rich.logging import RichHandler\r\n\r\nlogger.configure(handlers=[{\r\n    \"sink\":RichHandler(), \r\n    \"format\":\"<green>{time:YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss.SSS}</green> | <level>{level: <8}</level> | <cyan>{name}</cyan>:<cyan>{function}</cyan>:<cyan>{line}</cyan> - <level>{message}</level>\"\r\n}])\r\nlogger.debug(\"This is a debug statement\")\r\nlogger.info(\"This is an info statement\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow this works I tried doing:\r\n```python\r\nlogger.info(\"[bold red blink]Server is shutting down![/]\", extra={\"markup\": True})\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut it just literally prints the [bold red blink]\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17391902/87957850-b9dff480-caa8-11ea-8de8-683a7472e0f8.png)\r\n","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/661133885","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163#issuecomment-661133885","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163","id":661133885,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY2MTEzMzg4NQ==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-07-20T16:05:41Z","updated_at":"2020-07-20T16:05:41Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"The Rich handler renders date / level / file itself, which means it can format columns more nicely. But it does mean you can't configure it via the message format. \r\n\r\nAs for markup not working, that looks like a bug in loguru. According to stdlib docs, keys in `extra` should be copied to attributes of the log record. That doesn't appear to be happening. ","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/696103503","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163#issuecomment-696103503","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/163","id":696103503,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY5NjEwMzUwMw==","user":{"login":"remisphere","id":37183535,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM3MTgzNTM1","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/37183535?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere","html_url":"https://github.com/remisphere","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/remisphere/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-09-21T13:10:16Z","updated_at":"2020-09-21T13:20:15Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"@leej11, console markup works if you directly configure at the handler level rather than the log message, like this:\r\n```python\r\nfrom loguru import logger as log\r\nfrom rich.logging import RichHandler\r\n\r\nlog.configure(handlers=[{\"sink\": RichHandler(markup=True),\r\n                         \"format\": \"{message}\"}])\r\n```","performed_via_github_app":null}]